statement.p:
Find the volume inside the sphere \rho\le3 and inside the upper cone z\ge \sqrt{x^2+y^2}. The cone is 0\le\phi\le\frac{\pi}{4}. The full rotation around the z-axis gives 0\le\theta\le2\pi. So
V \amp= \int_0^{2\pi}\int_0^{\pi/4}\int_0^3 \rho^2\sin\phi\,d\rho\,d\phi\,d\theta \amp= (2\pi)\left(1-\cos\frac{\pi}{4}\right)\left(9\right) \amp= 18\pi\left(1-\frac{\sqrt2}{2}\right).
Thus \boxed{V=18\pi\left(1-\frac{\sqrt2}{2}\right).}

Suppose a planet has radius 3, and its density decreases linearly with distance from the center: \delta(\rho)=6-\rho, \qquad 0\le\rho\le3. Then
M \amp= 4\pi\int_0^3(6-\rho)\rho^2\,d\rho \amp= 4\pi\int_0^3(6\rho^2-\rho^3)\,d\rho \amp= 4\pi\left[2\rho^3-\frac{\rho^4}{4}\right]_0^3 \amp= 4\pi\left(54-\frac{81}{4}\right) \amp= 135\pi.
Thus \boxed{M=135\pi.}
